Technical SOP: SQL Job Monitoring & Reporting

Procedure Name: USP_SQL_Job_Run_Audit_And_Email

Description: Automates the tracking, logging, and email notification of SQL Server Agent job statuses.
==================
1. Objective
==================
To provide a daily automated report of all SQL Agent jobs, highlighting successes and failures in a single HTML email to ensure system reliability and quick troubleshooting.

==================
2. Workflow Logic
=================
The procedure follows a four-step automated cycle:
1.  Cleanup: Deletes any audit data previously logged for "Today" to prevent duplicate entries.
2.  Data Capture: Scans `msdb` system tables to find the "most recent" execution status for every job.
3.  Audit Logging: Saves these results into the "Job_Run_Status_Audit" table for historical tracking.
4.  Notification: Generates an HTML table where FAILED jobs are colored Red and SUCCEEDED jobs are Green**, then sends it via Database Mail.

==================
3. Key Components
==================
Audit Table: dbo.Job_Run_Status_Audit — Stores the job name, run time, duration, and status.
Mail Profile: Uses the "DBAlerts" profile.
Sorting: The email automatically groups failures at the top of the list for immediate visibility.


CREATE TABLE [dbo].[Job_Run_Status_Audit](
	[AuditID] [int] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
	[SerialNo] [int] NOT NULL,
	[JobName] [varchar](200) NOT NULL,
	[RunDateTime] [datetime] NULL,
	[RunDuration] [varchar](20) NULL,
	[JobStatus] [varchar](20) NULL,
	[AuditDate] [datetime] NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY CLUSTERED 
(
	[AuditID] ASC
)WITH (PAD_INDEX = OFF, STATISTICS_NORECOMPUTE = OFF, IGNORE_DUP_KEY = OFF, 
ALLOW_ROW_LOCKS = ON, ALLOW_PAGE_LOCKS = ON, OPTIMIZE_FOR_SEQUENTIAL_KEY = OFF) ON [PRIMARY]
) ON [PRIMARY]
GO
ALTER TABLE [dbo].[Job_Run_Status_Audit] ADD  DEFAULT (getdate()) FOR [AuditDate]

==============================
4. Configuration & Maintenance
==============================
 How to update recipients:
Locate the "EXEC msdb.dbo.sp_send_dbmail" section at the bottom of the script and modify the @recipients string:
> @recipients = 'yourname@example.com; team@example.com'

 How to exclude specific jobs:
Inside the "JobHistory" CTE, there is a commented-out "WHERE" clause. To hide specific jobs (like backups or cleanups) from the report:
1.  Uncomment the "AND j.name NOT IN (...)" block.
2.  Add the exact names of the jobs you wish to ignore.

===================
5. Troubleshooting
==================
Report is empty: Ensure jobs have actually run today and that the "msdb" history hasn't been purged.
Email not sending:  Run "SELECT * FROM msdb.dbo.sysmail_faileditems" to check for mail server errors.
Status says 'Unknown':** This occurs if a job has been created but has no execution history yet.

=============
6. Execution
============
Scheduled: Set to run via SQL Agent Job (e.g., every morning at 8:00 AM).
Manual: Run "EXEC [dbo].[USP_SQL_Job_Run_Audit_And_Email]" in SSMS.

===========================================================================================
--Stored Procedure

create or alter PROCEDURE [dbo].[USP_SQL_Job_Run_Audit_And_Email]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;
    DECLARE @Today DATE = CAST(GETDATE() AS DATE);
    --------------------------------------------------
    -- STEP 0: REMOVE TODAY'S OLD DATA
    --------------------------------------------------
    DELETE FROM dbo.Job_Run_Status_Audit
    WHERE CAST(AuditDate AS DATE) = @Today;
    --------------------------------------------------
    -- STEP 1: Capture Latest Job Status (Succeeded & Failed)
    --------------------------------------------------
    ;WITH JobHistory AS
    (
        SELECT
            j.job_id,
            j.name AS JobName,
            h.run_date,
            h.run_time,
            h.run_duration,
            h.run_status,
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
                PARTITION BY j.job_id
                ORDER BY h.run_date DESC, h.run_time DESC
            ) AS rn
        FROM msdb.dbo.sysjobs j
        LEFT JOIN msdb.dbo.sysjobhistory h
            ON j.job_id = h.job_id
        WHERE h.step_id = 0
   --     AND j.name NOT IN (                --Enable this if you want to ignore any job by inserting job names inplace of Job-1, Job-2
   --         'Job-1',
   --         'Job-2',
   --     )
    ),
    FinalData AS
    (
        SELECT
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY LTRIM(RTRIM(JobName))) AS SerialNo,
            JobName,

            CASE 
                WHEN run_date IS NOT NULL AND run_time IS NOT NULL THEN
                CONVERT(DATETIME,
                    STUFF(STUFF(CAST(run_date AS CHAR(8)),5,0,'-'),8,0,'-') + ' ' +
                    STUFF(STUFF(RIGHT('000000' + CAST(run_time AS VARCHAR(6)),6),3,0,':'),6,0,':')
                )
            END AS RunDateTime,

            CASE 
                WHEN run_duration IS NOT NULL THEN
                STUFF(STUFF(RIGHT('000000' + CAST(run_duration AS VARCHAR(6)),6),3,0,':'),6,0,':')
            END AS RunDuration,

            CASE run_status
                WHEN 0 THEN 'FAILED'
                WHEN 1 THEN 'SUCCEEDED'
                WHEN 2 THEN 'RETRY'
                WHEN 3 THEN 'CANCELLED'
                WHEN 4 THEN 'IN PROGRESS'
                ELSE 'UNKNOWN'
            END AS JobStatus,

            GETDATE() AS AuditDate
        FROM JobHistory
        WHERE rn = 1
    )

    INSERT INTO dbo.Job_Run_Status_Audit
    (
        SerialNo,
        JobName,
        RunDateTime,
        RunDuration,
        JobStatus,
        AuditDate
    )
    SELECT * FROM FinalData;

    --------------------------------------------------
    -- STEP 2: BUILD EMAIL CONTENT FOR ALL JOBS
    --------------------------------------------------
    DECLARE @body NVARCHAR(MAX) = '';
    DECLARE @rows NVARCHAR(MAX) = '';

    -- Capture Succeeded AND Failed jobs
    SELECT @rows =
    (
        SELECT 
            '<tr>' +
            '<td>' + CAST(SerialNo AS VARCHAR) + '</td>' +
            '<td style="text-align:left;">' + ISNULL(JobName,'') + '</td>' +
            '<td>' + ISNULL(CONVERT(VARCHAR, RunDateTime, 120),'') + '</td>' +
            '<td>' + ISNULL(RunDuration,'') + '</td>' +
            '<td style="font-weight:bold; color:' + 
                CASE WHEN JobStatus = 'FAILED' THEN 'red' ELSE 'green' END + ';">' + 
                ISNULL(JobStatus,'') + 
            '</td>' +
            '</tr>'
        FROM dbo.Job_Run_Status_Audit
        WHERE CAST(AuditDate AS DATE) = @Today
        ORDER BY JobStatus ASC, JobName ASC  -- Groups failures at the top
        FOR XML PATH(''), TYPE
    ).value('.', 'NVARCHAR(MAX)');

    --------------------------------------------------
    -- STEP 3: CONSTRUCT FINAL HTML & SEND
    --------------------------------------------------
    -- We removed the IF (@FailCount > 0) so the report always sends
    --------------------------------------------------
    -- STEP 3: CONSTRUCT FINAL HTML & SEND
    --------------------------------------------------
    SET @body =
    '<html>
    <head>
    <style>
        /* Change width to auto or a fixed px to stop the table from stretching too far */
        table { border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12px; width: auto; min-width: 600px; }
        th { background-color: #2F75B5; color: white; padding: 8px; white-space: nowrap; }
        td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 6px; text-align: center; }
        .header { font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    </style>
    </head>
    <body>

    <div class="header">Daily SQL Job Status Report - ' + CONVERT(VARCHAR, GETDATE(), 106) + '</div>

    <table>
        <tr>
            <th style="width: 50px;">Sr No</th>
            <th style="text-align:left; width: 300px;">Job Name</th> 
            <th style="width: 150px;">Run Date Time</th>
            <th style="width: 80px;">Duration</th>
            <th style="width: 100px;">Status</th>
        </tr>' 
        + ISNULL(@rows, '<tr><td colspan="5">No job history found for today.</td></tr>') +
    '</table>

    <br>Regards,<br>DBA Team
    </body>
    </html>';

    EXEC msdb.dbo.sp_send_dbmail
        @profile_name = 'DBAlerts',
        @recipients = 'praveensqldba12@gmail.com',
        @subject = 'SQL Jobs Execution Report',
        @body = @body,
        @body_format = 'HTML';

END
